text.tspan: Israel: Weekly confirmed COVID-19 cases by age, Israel
New confirmed cases are shown as the rolling weekly sum. Data is available at the national level, plus breakdown
by regions where vaccination began early or late.
Vaccination in Israel began on December 19 2020. Israel imposed a third national lockdown on January 8 2021.
Data source: Rossman, Shilo, Meir, Gorfine, Shalit & Segal (2021). Patterns of COVID-19 pandemic dynamics following
deployment of a broad national immunization program.
